I am certaily not a cosmetology expert, but I will put in my 2 cents.
It all depends on what your definition of traditional and latin is.
Salsa came about in the 1970s mostly in Miami and NYC,, in Miami the
culture was more from Cuba, in NYC it was more Puerto Rican.  From
what I remember the girls were wearing normal kight  evening make up
for the time.

Latin dance in general had roots in the sane areas, but the hub was
the Roseland Ballroom in Manhattan.  The makeup was probably a little
heavier than the later Salsa dancers.

You might check out Dirty Dancing II.  I think that it is prety
accurate as to the culture of early Larin dance.
